title: President Obama Visits Ethiopia | News
text:
President Obama making a historic visit to Ethiopia to discuss a host of issues. 
FOX News Radio’s Jessica Golloher has the details: Audio clip: Listen to audio clip. 
It’s a visit of firsts for President Obama here in Ethiopia. The first time a sitting U.S. president is visiting the East African nation and the first time an American president will address the African Union. This Ethiopian supports President Obama’s visit: 
(Ethiopian resident) “It’s nice. Happy for his coming because America is a developed country.” 
The president met with his Ethiopian counterpart and the country’s prime minister to discuss security issues, the economy and corruption. This as Al Shabab has claimed responsibility for a bombing that killed at least 13 in neighboring Somalia. 
In Addis Ababa, Jessica Golloher, FOX News Radio. Audio clip:
